{{Infobox website | name = Actustar | logo = | screenshot = | caption = | url = [http://www.actustar.com Actustar.com] | commercial = | type = [[Online magazine]], [[celebrity]], [[tabloid (newspaper format)|tabloid]], [[gossip]] | language = French | registration = | owner = Hi Media | author = | launch date = | alexa = | current status = Active | revenue = }}
'''''Actustar''''' is a French celebrity gossip [[online magazine]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20130403090840/http://www.magazine-cool.ca/actustar.html Magazine-cool.ca]</ref><ref>[http://www.hi-media.se/publishing/actustar.html?lang=se Hi-media.se] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130702153336/http://www.hi-media.se/publishing/actustar.html?lang=se |date=July 2, 2013 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.eonline.com/news/41718/tom-cruise-really-not-gay Eonline.com]</ref><ref>[http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/story?id=105826&page=1 ABC News]</ref> The magazine is part of Hi Media which acquired it in 2006.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hi Media : acquisitions de Jeuxvideo.com et Actustar.com|url=http://www.boursier.com/actions/actualites/news/hi-media-acquisitions-de-jeuxvideo-com-et-actustar-com-178095.html|accessdate=2 January 2016|work=Boursier|date=20 March 2006|language=French}}</ref> It is headquartered in Montigny Le Bretonneux, [[France]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Company Overview of Actustar.com|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=67071159|accessdate=2 January 2016|work=Bloomberg Business}}</ref>
==Controversy== ''Actustar'' on 13 March 2001 published an [[alleged]] interview with Kyle Bradford, in which he claimed that he and actor [[Tom Cruise]] had a [[homosexual]] [[affair]].<ref name=ActustarRum>[http://www.advocate.com/arts-entertainment/entertainment-news/2001/05/16/kyle-bradford-ltigtactustarltigt-both-denying-tom Advocate.com]</ref> The story also appeared in the [[mexico|Mexican]] [[Tabloid (newspaper format)|tabloid]] ''[[TVyNovelas]]''.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/hi/spanish/misc/newsid_1311000/1311376.stm|work=BBC News|title=Tom Cruise demanda a estrella porno|date=3 May 2001| accessdate=7 May 2010}}</ref> The affair supposedly occurred during Cruise's [[marriage]] to [[Nicole Kidman]] and Kidman's discovery of this [[secret]] relationship was related to their separation.<ref name=ActustarRum /> Cruise categorically denied the story and sued Bradford (Chad Slater) for $10 million.<ref>[http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-75248591.html Cruise control - actor Tom Cruise sues porn star for defamation - Brief Article | Advocate, The | Find Articles at BNET]</ref>
