* From 1998–2000 there was no Host Park, the awards were announced from Amusement Today's Arlington, Texas, office instead. The 2008 awards were announced at [[Give Kids the World Village]] in Orlando, Florida.
* 2017 was hosted by two parks.
==Repeat winners== * '''Best Amusement Park''' – [[Cedar Point]] for 16 of 21 years. * '''Best Amusement Park''' – [[Europa-Park]] for the last 5 years. * '''Best Water Park''' – [[Schlitterbahn]] for all 21 years. * '''Best Landscaping''' – [[Busch Gardens Williamsburg]] for all 21 years. * '''Best Children's Park''' – [[Idlewild and Soak Zone]] for the past 9 years. * '''Cleanest Park''' – [[Holiday World & Splashin' Safari|Holiday World]] for the last 15 years. * '''Friendliest Park''' – [[Holiday World & Splashin' Safari|Holiday World]] for 13 out of the last 17 years. * '''Best Halloween Event''' – [[Universal Studios Orlando]] for 9 out of the 11 years the award has been given. * '''Best Food''' – [[Knoebels]] for 16 out of last 17 years (tied once). * '''Best Kids Area''' – [[Kings Island]] for the last 18 years. * '''Best Steel Roller Coaster''' – [[Millennium Force]] for 10 of 21 years. * '''Best Steel Roller Coaster''' – [[Fury 325]] for the last 3 years. * '''Best Indoor Roller Coaster''' – [[Revenge of the Mummy]] for the last 11 years. * '''Best Shows''' – [[Dollywood]] for the last 10 years. * '''Best Indoor Waterpark''' – [[Schlitterbahn#Schlitterbahn Galveston Island|Schlitterbahn Galveston Island]] for all 8 years the award has been given. * ''' Best Outdoor Production Show''' – [[IllumiNations: Reflections of Earth]] at [[Epcot]] for 12 out of the 13 years the award has been given. * ''' Best Seaside Park''' – [[Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk]] for 11 of the last 12 years.
